#Spanish LLM (From Scratch)

#Overview

This project implements a lightweight Large Language Model trained from scratch for generating Spanish text.

The model is based on a GPT-style transformer architecture and is trained using Spanish Wikipedia data. It learns language patterns such as grammar, vocabulary, and sentence structure directly from raw text.

The goal is to build a compact, efficient Spanish language model suitable for experimentation and local deployment.


#Data

#Source:

Spanish Wikipedia (wikimedia/wikipedia, dump: 20231101.es)

Processing steps:

Loaded full Wikipedia dataset using HuggingFace datasets
Randomly shuffled dataset (seed = 42)
Selected a subset of 20,000 articles
Extracted only the "text" field

Final dataset:

Pure Spanish text corpus from Wikipedia
No additional preprocessing or cleaning applied

Tokenization
Tokenizer: Byte-Level BPE (trained from scratch)
Library: HuggingFace tokenizers

Configuration:

Vocabulary size: 20,000
Minimum frequency: 2
Special tokens:
<s> (BOS)
</s> (EOS)
<pad>
<unk>

Process:

Tokenizer trained directly on Spanish Wikipedia text
Converts raw text into subword token IDs
Enables efficient handling of rare and unknown words


#Dataset Preparation

Steps:

Convert raw text into HuggingFace Dataset
Tokenize text (no padding, truncation enabled)
Concatenate token sequences
Split into fixed-length chunks

Configuration:

Maximum sequence length: 128 tokens

Final format:

input_ids: tokenized sequences
labels: same as input (causal language modeling)


#Model Architecture
Model type: GPT-2 (from scratch)
Library: HuggingFace transformers

Configuration:

Vocabulary size: 20,000
Context length: 128
Embedding size: 512
Number of layers: 8
Number of attention heads: 8

#Training
Framework: HuggingFace Trainer
Task: Causal Language Modeling

Training settings:

Epochs: 1
Batch size: 4
Learning rate: 3e-4
Logging steps: 50
Checkpoint saving: every 500 steps
Mixed precision: Disabled (fp16=False)

Hardware support:

Uses Apple Metal (mps) if available
Falls back to CPU otherwise


#Pipeline

Spanish Wikipedia Text
   ↓
Tokenizer Training (Byte-Level BPE)
   ↓
Tokenization
   ↓
Chunking (128 tokens)
   ↓
GPT-2 Model Initialization
   ↓
Training (Trainer API)
   ↓
Model Saving
   ↓
Interactive Chat Interface


#Text Generation

The model generates text using probabilistic sampling.

Generation settings:

Max length: 100
Top-k sampling: 40
Top-p (nucleus): 0.9
Temperature: 0.7
Repetition penalty: 1.2


#Chat Interface

A simple CLI-based chat loop is included.

Usage:

Run the script
Enter prompts interactively
Type exit or quit to stop


You: Hola, ¿cómo estás?
AI: Hola, ¿cómo estás hoy? Me gustaría hablar sobre...

